      • removeReaction

        default void removeReaction(IMember member,
                            java.lang.String unicode)
        Remove a member's reaction on this message.
        Parameters:
        member - The member that reacted on the message.
        unicode - The unicode reaction.
        Throws:
        PermissionException - If the reaction to remove is not reacted by the identity itself, and the identity does not have Manager Messages permission.
        HigherHierarchyException -
        • If the member is the server owner.
        • If the member is at a higher or same hierarchy as the identity.
        ErrorResponseException - If the reaction is not found from the message's reactions.
        See Also:
        ErrorResponse.UNKNOWN_EMOJI
